president eduardo duhalde named a top aide anibal fernandez as minister of production filling a post left vacant for months as argentina endured the worst recession of its history the nomination of mr fernandez the president 's secretary came as argentina has started to show the first signs of economic recovery posting a trade surplus of 109 billion from january to august while maintaining a lid on inflation and keeping the peso more or less stable against the dollar mr duhalde 's first minister to oversee the crippled industrial sector jose ignacio de mendiguren resigned in april and the economy minister roberto lavagna took over the portfolio the transitional government will hand over power to a new administration by may after elections in march tony smith nyt

